HEADWORD: Trigness
<hw>Trig"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Trig</er>
trim, neat.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being trig; smartness;
neatness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their spars had no man-of-war <qex>trigness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Kane.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

